# This .dockerignore governs the CLIENT and SERVER image builds: both use the
# repository root as their build context (see docker-compose*.yml build.context: .)
# so their Dockerfiles can COPY the service directory and the repo-root shared/
# at build time. The mongo image builds from its own context with its own rules.
#
# Strategy: exclude everything, re-include the two app directories and shared/,
# then strip dependency trees, build output, and secrets so none ride into a layer.
*
!services/client
!services/server
!shared

# Never ship these into a layer. node_modules and build output are produced
# inside the image (npm ci / npm run build); the host's copies would only
# shadow them and bloat the context. package-lock.json is deliberately NOT
# excluded here — the server image needs it for `npm ci`.
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/build
**/.env
**/*.env
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/*.crt
**/certs
**/.vscode
**/*.log
